Objective: Learn how PowerShell can be used to manage an Active Directory.

Mission: Manage a server without a GUI by practicing PowerShell commands associated with Active Directory.

Environment & Tools: VirtualBox - Windows Server 2016 (Server1) and Windows 10 Client

Utilized PowerShell commands to complete the following:
1) Created an Organization Unit.
2) Created a new user account and password.
3) Created a global security group for users in specific department within newly created Organization Unit.
4) Added user from step 2 into group created in step 3
5) Added department parameter to user created in step 2

Created a PowerShell script to add domain users via a .csv file.
